accessibility.text: To shift right, a number is subtracted from x before squaring
For example, x2 shifted 4 right is (x-4)2 and 2x2+8x shifted 2 right is 2(x-2)2+8x

This works because it effectively shifts the x values going into the function. If you are subtracting 1 from x, it makes an x value of 1 produce the x value normally produced by 0, moving it 1 to the right. See the tables on the next slide for more information.
